The paper deals with approximation algorithms for a graph problem, specifically for unit disk graphs. This suggests that it could belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) categories. The problem also involves connectivity, which could place it in the Network Analysis and Algorithms (cs.NA) category. Additionally, the problem involves finding dominating sets, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. Finally, the paper involves approximation algorithms, which could place it in the Game Theory (cs.GT) category.
